# App-IDA-Daemon

A Mojolicious-based daemon that provides a low-level set of features
for implementing distributed (network-based) redundant storage systems
based on Michael O. Rabin's Information Dispersal Algorithm.

This README only contains minimal information: just enough for a quick
overview for someone browsing CPAN. For more detailed information, see:

* The included README.md file

* The App::IDA::Daemon documentation

* The package's [github page]

* The author's [other github repositories] for dependencies
  (particularly Crypt::IDA) and related bits of code.

[github page]: https://github.com/declanmalone/App-IDA-Daemon
[other github repositories]: https://github.com/declanmalone

## INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

## SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc App::IDA::Daemon

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=App-IDA-Daemon

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/App-IDA-Daemon

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/App-IDA-Daemon

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/App-IDA-Daemon/

